      "system": {
        "description": "<div class=\"boxgroup flexrow boxrow\">\n<div class=\"flexcol box\" style=\"justify-content: flex-start;\">\n<h4 class=\"nogrow\" style=\"margin: 0.5em;\">Features</h4>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 217\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Avian humanoid</p>\n<p>Long red nose</p>\n<p>Corvid feathering (crow, raven, jay) over red skin</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"flexcol box\" style=\"justify-content: flex-start;\">\n<h4 class=\"nogrow\" style=\"margin: 0.5em;\">Drives</h4>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 217\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Protect the mountains</p>\n<p>Collect trinkets and treasure</p>\n<p>Keep outsiders away</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"flexcol box\" style=\"justify-content: flex-start;\">\n<h4 class=\"nogrow\" style=\"margin: 0.5em;\">Tactics</h4>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 217\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Clawed attacks from above</p>\n<p>Drop rocks on victims</p>\n<p>Flock together to overwhelm</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 218\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 43\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>The Tengu people are avian in nature, but their bodies are not covered entirely in feathers. If it weren&rsquo;t for their red skin, wings, and comically long noses that may be an evolution from a beak, they could almost pass as a Firelander. Their feathering comes down from the top of their head to the back of their neck and shoulders before joining with their wings.</p>\n<p>Tengu are an ancient people who see it as their sacred duty to protect the mountains. As such, they dwell mainly in the Geppu Kyojin region and very much frown upon outsiders. They view us Firelanders as invaders and usurpers to the natural order. Miners and travelers are often met with a hail of arrows or rocks from above rather than a cordial greeting.</p>\n<p>One weakness or point of negotiation we can use with the Tengu is their love of treasure. Their self-imposed exile to the mountains limits their resources, so trade goods or items from the southern reaches of the Firelands are desirable gifts for them.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Quest Starter:</p>\n<p>A group of Tengu warriors have disrupted a mining camp just as they struck a vein of the precious nie iron. Is there any way to negotiate a truce, even if temporary, to be able to access the valuable ore?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 218\">\n<div class=\"section\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 43\">\n<div class=\"section\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<blockquote>\n<p><em>Your Truth:</em></p>\n<p><em>Are the Tengu truly avian in nature, or are do they have more demonic origins?</em></p>\n</blockquote>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>",
